case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_address_found_1: Roadside ditch 1/2 mile east from Correctionville, Iowa
case_circumstances: Human skeletal remains were discovered in a roadside ditch 1/2 mile east of Correctionville, Iowa in Woodbury County on August 30, 1988.  The remains were determined to be those of a white male with an estimated age range between 30 to 60 years.  The remains were estimated to measure 5 feet and 6 inches in height.  It is also estimated that the decedent died sometime between the years 1971 and 1973.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: Short sleeved plain colored shirt with button down collar.  One short sleeved white or pale yellow shirt.  One red, white and black plaid long sleeved button down shirt with "SL51" stenciled in the center of the neck band. Three pairs of socks.
case_footwear: Remains of 1 pair of shoes: soles of shoes have characters "7' DE" and "675" molded on the surface.
